node.text:
Here’s the narrative of the scene in “The Wolf of Wallstreet” as given by Jordan Belfort. If you’re selling to a customer, it’s important to make a personal connection and make your customer feel like you (the expert) knows exactly what they need, thus providing them with the product that fits their needs.
Could you sell Jordan a pen?

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The same information makes us react differently based on on the way it's presented. Politicians & marketers take advantage of this to twist data & numbers. @incomefact'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Let's say you're trying to cut down on fat. YOGURT YOGURT A. 20% Fat B.80% Fat Free Which yogurt would you rather get? @incomefact'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '80% 80% of people go for Logically both mean the same thing. But 80% fat free feels healthier. @incomefact'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'That's the power of of "framing." This is how people legally twist numbers & manipulate you. @incomefact'.
